%md
# Reading and manipulating canadian precipitation with Scispark

## Introduction
### Data
Daily precipitations over Canada in NetCDF format.
Available from this public [site](http://132.217.140.31:8083/thredds/catalog/birdhouse/nrcan/nrcan_canada_daily/catalog.html)

### Manipulation
As a simple demonstation of manipulation of data from Netcdf, an average of the data will calculated for two years, 1950 and 1951.
The average of the two years will be shown with Basemap.

paragraphs.text:
%md
## Loading data with Scispark
val dataListPath = "/Users/jfr/projects/scispark/mydata/pavics_list.txt"

import org.dia.core.SciSparkContext
val ssc = new SciSparkContext(sc)

val scientificRDD = ssc.netcdfFileList(dataListPath, 
List("lon", "lat", "time", "pr"))
.map(p1 => { // Adding the year from the file name to the metadata
    val yearStr =  p1.metaData("SOURCE").split("/").last.split("_").last.split("\\.")(0)
    p1.insertDictionary(("Year", yearStr))
    p1
})

%md
## Getting the mean precipitation
for 1950 and 1951.

The precipitation is available under the variable `pr` which is a tensor of 3 dimensions : Time, Latitude, Longitude.
To average over time (for the year), is calculated with the method `mean` and providing the dimension (axis=0 for time) to appy on.

Then we access the result with the method `data` which flattens the 2tensor values (corresponding to latitude and longitude)

val prArray1950 = scientificRDD
    .filter(p => p.metaData("Year").toInt == 1950)
    .map(p => p("pr").mean(0).data)
    .first()

val prArray1951 = scientificRDD
    .filter(p => p.metaData("Year").toInt == 1951)
    .map(p => p("pr").mean(0).data)
    .first()

paragraphs.text:
%md
### from scala to python with tempview

// Keeping the index to allow preservation of orders
val lon = scientificRDD.map(p => p("lon").data).first
val lat = scientificRDD.map(p => p("lat").data).first
val dfLat = sc.parallelize(lat.zipWithIndex).toDF("lat", "idx")
val dfLon = sc.parallelize(lon.zipWithIndex).toDF("lon", "idx")
dfLon.createOrReplaceTempView("lons")
dfLat.createOrReplaceTempView("lats")

%pyspark
pyDflons = sqlContext.sql('SELECT idx, lon FROM lons ORDER BY idx')
pyDflats = sqlContext.sql('SELECT idx, lat FROM lats ORDER BY idx')
pyDfPr1950 =  sqlContext.sql('SELECT idx, year_1950 FROM prs ORDER BY idx')
pyDfPr1951 =  sqlContext.sql('SELECT idx, year_1951 FROM prs ORDER BY idx')

%md

### Create reshaped numpy array

%pyspark
import numpy as np

np_lat = np.asarray(pyDflats.select("lat").rdd.flatMap(lambda x : x).collect())
np_lon = np.asarray(pyDflons.select("lon").rdd.flatMap(lambda x : x).collect())
np_pr_1950 = np.asarray(pyDfPr1950.select("year_1950").rdd.flatMap(lambda x : x).collect())
np_pr_1951 = np.asarray(pyDfPr1951.select("year_1951").rdd.flatMap(lambda x : x).collect())

%pyspark
prReshape1950 = np.asarray(np_pr_1950).reshape(len(np_lat), len(np_lon))
prReshape1951 = np.asarray(np_pr_1951).reshape(len(np_lat), len(np_lon))
